During a press briefing, White House Deputy Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre announced that the popular South Korean boy band BTS would be joining President Biden in a discussion about Asian inclusion, representation, and diversity. The band, known for promoting a message of respect and positivity, would be meeting with the president to address anti-Asian hate crimes and discrimination. Jean-Pierre mentioned that the president has been committed to combating racism and xenophobia since his first week in office, and has taken several actions to address these issues. The briefing also covered topics such as the Federal Reserve, inflation, gun control, and the president's meeting with the New Zealand Prime Minister.